es the energy of polarization\ninhomogeneities is observed experimentally, which is in disagreement with the\nmodel expectations. Specifics of this dependence suggest the presence of a\nnearly temperature-independent characteristic length scale for inhomogeneities\nacross several phases. Other differences with the model suggest that the\nincommensurate order parameter cannot be straightforwardly identified with\nweakly-inhomogeneous ferroelectric polarization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Oct 2021 14:08:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-19"}
